21:07.733 --> 21:12.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for officials who ran what
they call sanctuary cities.

21:14.733 --> 21:18.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the lieutenant governor was
placing blame for this incident
on cities and counties that

21:20.366 --> 21:22.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
don't cooperate with federal
immigration officials.

21:22.333 --> 21:26.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Well, it's a
horrible, horrible incident,
reminds us of the people behind

21:26.733 --> 21:27.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
these issues.

21:27.966 --> 21:30.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Jason Buch, thanks so
much for joining us.

21:30.866 --> 21:35.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JASON BUCH: Thank you.

21:38.633 --> 21:43.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Stay with us.

21:43.266 --> 21:47.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour":
I sit down with Tom Perez, the
chair of the Democratic National

21:47.766 --> 21:52.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Committee; our Politics
Monday duo examines the
Democrats and the latest
White House controversies;

21:55.200 --> 22:00.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and a new film documents
the lives of Syrian
activists battling ISIS.

22:01.833 --> 22:05.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But, first, we turn
to Bangladesh and the
plight of the Rohingya.

22:07.333 --> 22:10.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They are an ethnic minority
group seeking refuge there,
many having been forced from

22:10.233 --> 22:12.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
their homes in
neighboring Myanmar.

22:12.733 --> 22:17.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But as special correspondent
Tania Rashid found,
they are hardly more
welcome in Bangladesh.

22:19.166 --> 22:22.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
By the tens of thousands, they
are stuck in a deadly limbo.

22:22.666 --> 22:26.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And a warning: Parts of this
story may disturb some viewers.

22:26.300 --> 22:31.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TANIA RASHID: The island is
isolated, covered in bushes,
and underwater half of the year.

22:33.533 --> 22:38.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's called Thenga Chor, and it
lies on the coast of Bangladesh.

22:38.133 --> 22:41.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a hard and long day's boat
ride from the nearest port.

22:41.733 --> 22:46.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This rough spot might be the
new home for the Rohingya,
a group of more than 300,000

22:48.400 --> 22:51.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
people the U.N. calls
the most persecuted
minority in the world.

22:51.133 --> 22:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But on a camp on the mainland,
Hafez, a Rohingya activist,
says that is no place they want

22:56.800 --> 22:58.766 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to go.

22:58.766 --> 23:01.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HAFEZ, Activist (through
translator): If we go to
Thenga Chor, we will get sick.

23:01.900 --> 23:03.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We can die.

23:03.366 --> 23:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We are used to being here,
and we feel safe here.

23:05.500 --> 23:08.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
TANIA RASHID: It's
only a relative safety.

23:08.233 --> 23:13.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Close to half-a-million have
fled murder and persecution
by the army of Myanmar to seek

23:13.066 --> 23:16.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
refuge in camps in
Southern Bangladesh.

23:16.266 --> 23:21.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Muslim Rohingya have
lived in mainly Buddhist
Myanmar for centuries,
but are viewed as illegal

23:22.433 --> 23:24.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ethnic Bangladeshis by
the Myanmar government.

23:24.433 --> 23:29.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The de facto leader of Myanmar,
Nobel peace laureate Aung San
Suu Kyi, has denied a U.N.

23:30.533 --> 23:33.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
charge of ethnic cleansing
of the Rohingya'.

23:33.600 --> 23:38.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But in the last eight months,
the numbers of Rohingya fleeing
for their lives have surged

23:39.333 --> 23:41.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to more than 70,000.

23:41.433 --> 23:45.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But now their lives are more
precarious than ever before.

23:45.233 --> 23:49.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Monsoon season and a
punishing cyclone damaged
many Rohingya settlements.

23:49.833 --> 23:54.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the Bangladeshi government
plans to resolve the Rohingya's
continued displacement by moving

23:56.066 --> 23:58.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
60,000 of the refugees
to this remote island.

23:58.666 --> 24:03.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Aid agencies like the UNHCR
and Human Rights Watch have
expressed alarm over the planned

24:04.966 --> 24:06.166 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
relocation.

24:06.166 --> 24:08.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Our journey to the
island was difficult.

24:08.566 --> 24:11.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We began a week
before the cyclone.

24:11.533 --> 24:16.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We traveled first by ferry,
then by a private boat, where a
local fishermen agreed to take

24:17.266 --> 24:18.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
us to the island.

24:18.966 --> 24:20.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It was a dangerous journey.

24:20.933 --> 24:24.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Pirates are known to
control these seas and
take hostages for ransom.

24:24.500 --> 24:27.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
But the island is
not easy to access.

24:27.200 --> 24:32.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The tides are too high on
the bigger ship, so we had to
get a smaller boat to take us

24:32.800 --> 24:33.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to the island.

24:33.733 --> 24:38.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We just made it on the island.

24:40.233 --> 24:43.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We managed to find a muddy
bog to land near, and get
us across to the island.

24:43.233 --> 24:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The government has already
moved forward with the plan of
making the island more habitable

24:48.966 --> 24:51.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
by planting trees.

24:51.066 --> 24:54.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But this local official
doesn't want the Rohingyas
moving into his district.

24:56.333 --> 24:58.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He thinks it will create more
problems for his community.

24:58.766 --> 25:01.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MINAZUR RAHMAN, Local
Official (through
translator): In the past,
the Rohingya were related to

25:01.633 --> 25:03.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the drug problem.

25:03.066 --> 25:05.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They are linked to drugs,
linked to smuggling.

25:05.300 --> 25:07.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Most of the people here, their
main livelihood is fishing.

25:07.900 --> 25:11.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The bad character and influence
of the Rohingya people will
impact the locals here.

25:11.966 --> 25:15.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
TANIA RASHID: But the
Bangladeshi government
believe the Rohingyas
cross the border at

25:15.933 --> 25:19.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
will, with the help of smugglers
and corrupt border guards.

25:19.700 --> 25:23.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The government argues the
relocation will guarantee their
isolation from the rest of

25:23.800 --> 25:25.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the population.

25:25.766 --> 25:29.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But the island is formed by
river sediment, making it
unstable, and it could be eroded

25:29.700 --> 25:31.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in five years' time.

25:31.700 --> 25:35.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dr. Ainun Nishat is a
leading expert on climate
change in Bangladesh.

25:35.400 --> 25:37.466 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

25:37.466 --> 25:38.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
AINUN NISHAT, Climate Change
Expert: The main history of
the coastal belt of Bangladesh

25:38.966 --> 25:43.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
is highly vulnerable to storm
surges and cyclonic weather.

25:45.733 --> 25:49.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Due to impact of climate change,
we believe that the frequency
of climate change may not

25:51.933 --> 25:56.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
be increasing, but intensity
of the storm surges are
definitely going to increase.

25:56.700 --> 26:01.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, they should be accommodated
in good concrete structure,
where at the time of emergency

26:05.166 --> 26:09.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
people should we -- can
be moved to a height
of 20 feet and above.

26:09.400 --> 26:14.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TANIA RASHID: Today, about
one million Rohingyas
live in apartheid-like
conditions in internment

26:16.366 --> 26:19.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
camps in Rakhine State of
Myanmar, separated from
the Buddhist majority.

26:21.766 --> 26:24.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They have no citizenship, and
need permission to marry or
to travel outside of their own

26:25.433 --> 26:27.433 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
villages.

26:27.433 --> 26:30.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
On October 9 of last year,
Rohingya militants killed
nine Myanmar police officers.

26:32.900 --> 26:36.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Myanmar military
then led a wide and
brutal counterinsurgency
campaign in retaliation,

26:38.866 --> 26:42.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where they killed more
than 1,000 Rohingyas,
torched homes and mosques.

26:42.733 --> 26:47.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Myanmar government calls
these accusations exaggerations
and denies charges of ethnic

26:47.700 --> 26:49.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
cleansing.

26:49.366 --> 26:53.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Dil Nawaz is one of
70,000 Rohingya's who
fled to Bangladesh.

26:53.400 --> 26:58.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She was gang-raped by soldiers,
and witnessed her husband's
murder in front of her eyes.

26:58.133 --> 27:03.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I'm looking at a photo of
her husband who was hacked to
death about five months ago,

27:04.666 --> 27:06.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
and this is a photograph
she took shortly after
she was murdered.

27:06.666 --> 27:11.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DIL NAWAZ, Refugee (through
translator): They used a machete
on my husband in front of me

27:11.200 --> 27:12.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
on the road.

27:12.200 --> 27:13.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I saw it with my own eyes.

27:13.800 --> 27:18.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They chopped him into pieces
in front of me in a rice field.

27:18.000 --> 27:23.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, the army came and took
all the women out to the rice
fields and took several women.

27:23.866 --> 27:26.066 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Five men took turns raping them.

27:26.066 --> 27:30.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They took people's gold
jewelry, rings and earrings.

27:30.533 --> 27:32.366 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They killed some children.

27:32.366 --> 27:36.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then they burned all the houses
down, followed by the mosque.

27:36.233 --> 27:39.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Then the military went
back to a Buddhist area.

27:39.200 --> 27:41.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This is why we
fled to Bangladesh.

27:41.433 --> 27:46.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
TANIA RASHID: Activist
Hafez says they have
found refuge here.

27:46.100 --> 27:49.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HAFEZ (through translator):
Bangladesh is small, and
overpopulated, but they gave us

27:49.900 --> 27:51.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a place to stand.

27:51.500 --> 27:53.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is a big thing.

27:53.466 --> 27:57.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TANIA RASHID: But like many
other Rohingya, he wants
a sense of permanence.

27:57.133 --> 28:01.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HAFEZ (through translator):
Instead of sending us to Thenga
Chor, if the Myanmar government

28:01.733 --> 28:05.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
could, we request that
they grant us citizenship.

28:05.066 --> 28:09.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
TANIA RASHID: Forty-five-year
old Dilbar hopes for a
last-ditch political solution.

28:09.633 --> 28:14.166 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DILBAR, Refugee (through
translator): If the
Bangladesh government and
the Myanmar government

28:14.166 --> 28:17.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
negotiate a deal and send us
back, then we will be happy.

28:17.400 --> 28:20.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
If this doesn't happen,
then please bomb us.

28:20.900 --> 28:23.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We came here, left
our homes, rice.

28:23.833 --> 28:26.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We came here to save our lives.

28:26.033 --> 28:29.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
If we have no peace,
then it's better to die.

28:29.666 --> 28:30.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Our children died there.

28:30.966 --> 28:34.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We sacrificed everything
and came here for peace.

28:34.466 --> 28:39.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
If you take us to the
island, it will be like
killing us, slaughtering us.

28:40.333 --> 28:41.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We are like Anthony Scaramucci.

28:41.300 --> 28:42.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
We are nothing.

28:42.333 --> 28:44.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It won't take much to kill us.

28:44.333 --> 28:46.366 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Just bomb us.

28:46.366 --> 28:50.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nobody will make a case
against you, because we have
no ground under our feet.

28:50.233 --> 28:53.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
TANIA RASHID: Their hope, to
find that safe ground one day.

28:53.733 --> 28:58.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, for now, they remain
in limbo, not of this land
and not pushed from it.

29:00.800 --> 29:05.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm Tania Rashid on Thenga
Chor Island, Bangladesh.

29:15.033 --> 29:20.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now to our series
of conversations focusing on the
road ahead for the Democratic

29:24.700 --> 29:26.733 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Party.

29:26.733 --> 29:30.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
