29:50.300 --> 29:52.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You don't blink.

29:52.400 --> 29:55.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You look in the mirror and
ask, what did we do wrong?

29:55.800 --> 30:00.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The number one thing we did
wrong is not present a strong,
bold economic agenda to working

30:04.200 --> 30:08.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Americans, so that their
hope for the future
might return again.

30:08.000 --> 30:10.066 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

30:10.066 --> 30:12.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NANCY PELOSI (D-CA), House
Minority Leader: That is why,
today, Democrats are unveiling

30:12.100 --> 30:17.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
an aggressive and ambitious
economic agenda, and a bold new
promise to America's working

30:18.666 --> 30:20.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
families.

30:20.633 --> 30:24.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
From the heartland -- these
members are from the heartland,
but to the suburbs, to the

30:24.833 --> 30:29.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
cities, Democrats are offering
a better deal, better jobs,
better wages, a better future.

30:32.066 --> 30:34.066 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
REP.

30:34.066 --> 30:36.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BEN RAY LUJAN (D), New
Mexico: Voters, constituents
want us to focus on them.

30:36.600 --> 30:38.866 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They want us to
understand where they are.

30:38.866 --> 30:42.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they want us to understand
that their wages are not
keeping up with their cost of

30:42.466 --> 30:44.500 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
living.

30:44.500 --> 30:46.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so the more people that are
able to have that conversation
with the American people,

30:46.400 --> 30:49.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
we will be in a
stronger place in 2018.

30:49.100 --> 30:54.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Joining me now
to discuss the new agenda, and
the way forward for the party,

30:55.766 --> 30:57.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
is the chairman of the
Democratic National
Committee, Tom Perez.

30:57.866 --> 31:00.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Welcome to the "NewsHour."

31:00.000 --> 31:04.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, how did the Democratic Party
get to the point where you have
to be reintroducing yourselves

31:05.333 --> 31:07.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to the American people, telling
them what you stand for?

31:07.400 --> 31:08.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
THOMAS PEREZ, Chairman,
Democratic National
Committee: Well, we have
heard across America

31:08.866 --> 31:12.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
from people that they don't
know what we stand for.

31:12.166 --> 31:14.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I have been traveling
to countries listening.

31:14.633 --> 31:19.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so what Leader Pelosi,
Senator Schumer and others
today have been doing is telling

31:19.233 --> 31:22.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
people not only what
we're fighting for, but
who we're fighting for.

31:22.300 --> 31:24.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're fighting for a
better future for everyone.

